  <bioghist id="aspace_246dd088f4e835a0fae5e64145c25a67">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Barry M. Goldwater, an Arizona senator, was a United States presidential candidate in 1964.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_32a1719860e621eed9831b4a6e0f2815">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Largely 1964 campaign letters, newspaper clippings, pamphlets, and other materials from various sources, including Republican National Committee members, national and local political figures, and individual voters and their children. Subjects included are conservatism, the Republican National Committee, gun control, Medicare, civil rights, and the John Birch Society.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_20a9b8df6614afbe0ed398eca40e08b8">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Barry Goldwater papers, #2616. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
